<html lang="en">

<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <link rel="icon" href="/img/weather.png">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css" />
  <title>Document</title>
</head>

<body>
  <div class="main-content">
    {{>header}}
    <section class="how-to-use">
      <h2>🌤️ How to Use the Weather App</h2>
      <ol class="steps">
        <li>Enter the name of a city in the search box.</li>
        <li>Click the <strong>"Get Weather"</strong> button.</li>
        <li>The app will fetch and display the latest weather information including:
          <ul>
            <li>🌡️ Temperature</li>
            <li>⛅ Description (like cloudy, sunny, rainy)</li>
            <li>🤗 Feels like</li>
            <li>💧 Humidity</li>
          </ul>
        </li>
      </ol>

      <div class="note">
        <h3>🔐 If you get an error or no result:</h3>
        <ul>
          <li>Make sure the city name is spelled correctly.</li>
          <li>The app relies on a weather API, so data accuracy depends on the source.</li>
          <li>Try refreshing or using a different city if results seem off.</li>
        </ul>
      </div>

      <p class="support">💬 Still stuck? Feel free to <a href="https://github.com/siddhant197/node-weather-app/issues"
          target="_blank">raise an issue on GitHub</a> or reach out for support!</p>
    </section>
  </div>

  {{>footer}}
</body>

</html>